text: Flurence Moore (17 November 1890 – 13 December 1953) was an Australian rules football player. ==Playing career== After beginning his career for Boulder City in Western Australia, Moore moved to Essendon, playing seven matches during the 1915 VFL season. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1890 births Category:1953 deaths Category:Essendon Football Club players Category:Boulder City Football Club players Category:Australian rules footballers from Western Australia
